SELECT record_id, experiment_name, timestamp FROM error_correction_results ORDER BY timestamp DESC

SELECT experiment_name, count(*) AS total_count FROM error_correction_results GROUP BY experiment_name
SELECT * FROM error_correction_results WHERE error_rate > 0.5 ORDER BY timestamp DESC
SELECT experiment_name, COUNT(*) AS num_records FROM error_correction_results GROUP BY experiment_name HAVING num_records > 5
SELECT * FROM error_correction_results ORDER BY error_rate ASC, timestamp DESC

SELECT experiment_id, error_correction_success_rate, timestamp FROM QuantumErrorCorrectionResults JOIN ErrorCorrectionMetadata ON QuantumErrorCorrectionResults.experiment_id = ErrorCorrectionMetadata.experiment_id WHERE ErrorCorrectionMetadata.error_code = 'X' ORDER BY QuantumErrorCorrectionResults.timestamp ASC;
SELECT MAX(error_correction_success_rate) AS max_success_rate FROM QuantumErrorCorrectionResults;

SELECT AVG(error_correction_success_rate) AS avg_success_rate, MIN(error_correction_success_rate) AS min_success_rate FROM QuantumErrorCorrectionResults WHERE timestamp >= '2021-01-01' AND timestamp <= '2022-01-01';
